    <!-- Section 5: FTS Holding Structures -->
    <section id="section-5">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>How FTS Investors Actually Hold &mdash; and Exit</h2>
            <p>The FTS market has systematically engineered away genuine equity exposure. Each innovation reduces the investor's contact with the underlying exploration venture.</p>

            <div class="holding-grid">
                <div class="holding-card">
                    <h3>Traditional LP</h3>
                    <div class="hold-period">18&ndash;24 mo</div>
                    <p>Subscribe at year-end, LP dissolves and rolls over into resource mutual fund. No secondary market during term.</p>
                    <div class="cite"><a href="https://ca.rbcwealthmanagement.com/documents/634020/3210246/The+Navigator+-+Flow-Through+Shares+and+Limited+Partnership+Units.pdf">RBC Wealth Management</a></div>
                </div>
                <div class="holding-card">
                    <h3>Short-Duration LP</h3>
                    <div class="hold-period">6&ndash;12 mo</div>
                    <p>Compressed timeline targets investors who want the deduction with minimal equity exposure.</p>
                    <div class="cite"><a href="https://www.ninepoint.com/about-ninepoint/press-releases/ninepoint-2025-flow-through-limited-partnership-announces-rollover-transaction-and-dissolution/">Ninepoint 2025</a></div>
                </div>
                <div class="holding-card">
                    <h3>Charity Donation</h3>
                    <div class="hold-period">Same day</div>
                    <p>Subscribe, donate to charity, charity sells to liquidity provider &mdash; all three steps close same day. After-tax cost of giving: 2&ndash;10%.</p>
                    <div class="cite"><a href="https://peartreecanada.com/">PearTree Canada</a> &middot; $500M+/year</div>
                </div>
                <div class="holding-card highlight">
                    <h3>EIS/SEIS (contrast)</h3>
                    <div class="hold-period">3+ years</div>
                    <p>Credit clawed back if sold early. CGT exemption only after 3-year hold. Early exit <em>destroys</em> the tax benefit.</p>
                    <div class="cite"><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/venture-capital-schemes-apply-to-use-the-enterprise-investment-scheme">HMRC EIS Guidance</a></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">FTS are issued at a <strong>20&ndash;30% premium</strong> over common share price for CEE expenses, and 8&ndash;15% for CDE (<a href="https://www.miningtaxcanada.com/flow-through-shares/">Mining Tax Canada</a>; <a href="https://blog.cfoplus.boutique/flow-through-fundamentals-what-canadian-mining-executives-need-to-know-in-2025/">CFOplus 2025</a>). The premium reflects the tax value &mdash; but the nil cost base means <em>all</em> proceeds on sale are taxable as gains. Premium-sharing dynamics were modelled by <a href="https://www.ctf.ca/common/Uploaded%20files/Documents/PDF/1996ctj/1996CTJ4_Jog.pdf">Jog, Lenjosek &amp; McKenzie (1996)</a>, who found that effectiveness depends critically on whether the premium compensates for underlying equity risk.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

