            <h2>The Path Forward</h2>
            <p>Four policy steps to close the innovation investment incentive gap:</p>
            <div class="path-grid">
                <div class="path-card">
                    <span class="path-step-number">1</span>
                    <h3>Innovation FTS</h3>
                    <p>Extend flow-through share deduction to SR&ED-eligible companies in tech, cleantech, life sciences, and advanced manufacturing. Uses proven Canadian legislative framework. <a href="https://www.blg.com/en/insights/2025/ri/the-expansion-of-flow-through-shares-to-innovation-waiting-for-godot">BLG (Nov 2025)</a> has published detailed analysis of how this could work.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="path-card">
                    <span class="path-step-number">2</span>
                    <h3>Add EIS Features</h3>
                    <p>Layer CGT exemption on 3+ year holds and loss relief against income &mdash; addressing the nil cost base problem and creating alignment incentives that the current FTS model lacks. <a href="https://cdhowe.org/publication/flow-through-shares-could-ignite-tech-innovation/">C.D. Howe</a> estimates $500M annually in new startup investment.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="path-card">
                    <span class="path-step-number">3</span>
                    <h3>Platform Integration</h3>
                    <p>Connect with OSC-regulated equity crowdfunding platforms (MI 45-108, proposed MI 45-111) to lower friction and bring retail investors into innovation ventures at scale &mdash; replicating the UK's EIS + Seedrs/Crowdcube ecosystem.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="path-card">
                    <span class="path-step-number">4</span>
                    <h3>Ontario Provincial Credit</h3>
                    <p>Ontario creates a 10&ndash;15% provincial innovation investment tax credit (analogous to OFFTS) as proof-of-concept. Within Ontario's fiscal authority; doesn't require federal action. OSC could play advisory/design role.</p>
                </div>
